        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Woodlawn, or near Galax, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Galax...
Hillsville...
Sparta...
Independence...
Fries...
and Fancy Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
